Drop redundant cfg/sts prefixes from DUT members (breaking)

`dev.cfg.cfgInputType` and `dev.sts.stsValue` were noisy — the container
already names the role, so repeating it on every member was just visual
clutter. This sweep drops the `cfg` prefix from every `ST_*_Cfg` member
and the `sts` prefix from every `ST_*_Sts` / `ST_DeviceHeader_Sts` /
faceplate DUT member, giving a consistent "container names the role,
member is just a name" style throughout the library.

Rename scope (word-boundary regex, driven by a one-shot PowerShell
script that has since been removed):

  cfg DUTs (ST_AnalogInput_Cfg, ST_AnalogOutput_Cfg, ST_DigitalInput_Cfg,
  ST_DigitalOutput_Cfg, ST_TwoPosActuator_Cfg):
    cfgInputType / cfgOutputType / cfgUseRawValue /
    cfgRawMin / cfgRawMax / cfgEuMin / cfgEuMax / cfgUnit /
    cfgClampAsFault / cfgFilterTau / cfgQualityFaultAfter /
    cfgMinCv / cfgMaxCv /
    cfgInvert / cfgDebounceOn / cfgDebounceOff /
    cfgMode / cfgPulseOn / cfgPulseOff /
    cfgAdvTimeoutS / cfgRetTimeoutS /
    cfgHoldAtAdvanced / cfgHoldAtRetracted
      -> prefix dropped

  sts DUTs (ST_AnalogInput_Sts, ST_AnalogOutput_Sts, ST_DigitalInput_Sts,
  ST_DigitalOutput_Sts, ST_DeviceHeader_Sts, ST_TwoPosActuator_Sts,
  ST_Alarm_Sts, ST_AlarmLimit_Sts):
    stsValue / stsRawReal / stsScaled / stsUnit / stsQuality /
    stsClampedLow / stsClampedHigh / stsClampActive /
    stsCommanded / stsRawValue / stsRisingEdge / stsFallingEdge /
    stsReady / stsBusy / stsFaulted / stsSourceLocked /
    stsAdvanced / stsRetracted / stsMoving /
    stsEnabled / stsRaw / stsDebounced / stsActive / stsLatched / stsAcked /
    stsHiHiActive / stsHiActive / stsLoActive / stsLoLoActive / stsAnyActive
      -> prefix dropped

  Faceplate DUTs (ST_Permissive_Faceplate, ST_Interlock_Faceplate):
    stsOK -> ok, stsLive -> live, stsMapped -> mapped,
    stsBypassed -> bypassed, cfgBypassable -> bypassable

Not renamed (intentionally):
  - `faultCode`, `lastFaultString`, `tsLastCommand`, `stateString`
    etc. — already unprefixed, already in the target style.
  - `inp*` on VAR_INPUT and `_private` on FB internals — these signal
    *visibility*, not *role*, and are a different pattern entirely.
  - Local method parameters like `FB_AlarmBase._Evaluate(cfgCommon := ...)`
    and FB_StateMachine's `cfgAutoRun` VAR_INPUT — not DUT members.

Updated in one sweep:
  - every library FB body that read/wrote these fields
  - all DUT declarations
  - TcForgeExample (GVL_HW, GVL_ALARMS, PRG_Alarms)
  - entire unit-test suite (probes + tests)
  - docs (1-Programming-Standards, 2-Architecture, 5-IO-Binding, 8-Alarms)
  - CHANGELOG with a BREAKING callout and a migration note

Verified:
  - Full solution builds with 0 warnings.
  - All 118 TcUnit tests across 12 suites pass on the remote runtime
    (172.18.236.100.1.1).

Migration: application code that referenced the old names needs a
mechanical search/replace following the list above.
